Build tool that generates two C++ headers (`steno_generated_dictionary_data.h` and `steno_generated_testdata.h`) from `dict.infinite.steno`, which feed the javelin-ext replay dictionary. The pipeline parses the source, runs Pass A to count operations, builds type and construct tables, checks for fuse ambiguity as a guard before emission, then writes both headers to `out/`. Notably, Pass B (the expensive `O(T^s)` enumeration) is skipped entirely — the lookup walk happens per-query instead, making this generator fast enough to run in the build (sibling of `build_dict.rs`; the two corpora build independently).

The two headers land in the same output directory: the data header is self-contained and included by the dictionary; the test header pins that dictionary to the Rust reference walker (D9, a specific decision point). The tool reads from the workspace root and assumes `dict.infinite.steno` and `out/` both exist there.

`run()` loads and parses the source via `parse_source()`, builds tables with `build_tables()`, guards against fuse ambiguity with `check_fuse_ambiguity()`, then emits both via `emit_data_header()` and `emit_test_header()`. All errors bubble up as strings; `main()` converts them to stderr output and failure exit code.